==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Isochromatic
<hw>I`so*chro*mat"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Iso-</ets> + <ets>chromatic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Opt.)</fld>
<def>Having the same color; connecting parts having the same color, as
lines drawn through certain points in experiments on the chromatic
effects of polarized light in crystals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isochronal</ent>⟦br⟧
